"WRP-2225 was put in place to improve efficienct/pass-through of EDI docs.  One of the changes was to make sure any EDI that did not plug a member did then not go to KE.  In the case of multiple, yet not-pluggable, matches EDI would go to KE and present a \042member not found\042 reject.  That was a waste of time.  Instead, this is now recognized and the reject is set.  - jdm 07/2018"
"Due to an issue with there suddenly being 200k+ rows in the dB with all zeros for an ID we are now skipping lookups on that ID - jdm 06/2015"

"If so the ID-based lookup(s) either didn't produce results or the keyer chose No Good Match.  By using a flag to indicate this lookup needs to run it stops us from having to repeat the code tree everywhere the name-based lookup needs to run.  Basically: instead of having the exact same tree as below here once it would be everywhere the Flag is set to 1.  That saves a lot of memory and disk space."
